Document: PathFollow3D
Path: godot/classes/class_pathfollow3d.rst
Summary: Describes the PathFollow3D node, which makes other nodes follow a Path3D.
This node takes its parent Path3D, and returns the coordinates of a point within it, given a distance from the first vertex. It is useful for making other nodes follow a path, without coding the movement pattern. For that, the nodes must be children of this node. The descendant nodes will then move accordingly when setting the progress in this node.
---CHUNK---
Document: PathFollow3D
Path: godot/classes/class_pathfollow3d.rst
Summary: Defines the properties that control the behavior and positioning of a PathFollow3D node.

Properties
* cubic_interp (bool): If true, the path will be interpolated using cubic interpolation. Default: true
* h_offset (float): The horizontal offset along the path. Default: 0.0
* loop (bool): If true, the path will loop. Default: true
* progress (float): The current progress along the path in units. Default: 0.0
* progress_ratio (float): The current progress along the path as a ratio (0.0 to 1.0). Default: 0.0
* rotation_mode (RotationMode): Determines how the node rotates relative to the path. Default: 3
* tilt_enabled (bool): If true, the node will tilt to follow the path's curvature. Default: true
* use_model_front (bool): If true, the node's forward direction will align with the path's direction. Default: false
* v_offset (float): The vertical offset along the path. Default: 0.0
---CHUNK---
Document: PathFollow3D
Path: godot/classes/class_pathfollow3d.rst
Summary: Defines rotation modes for PathFollow3D nodes and explains their behavior.

Enumerations
enum RotationMode:
  ROTATION_NONE = 0
    Forbids the PathFollow3D to rotate.
  ROTATION_Y = 1
    Allows the PathFollow3D to rotate in the Y axis only.
  ROTATION_XY = 2
    Allows the PathFollow3D to rotate in both the X, and Y axes.
  ROTATION_XYZ = 3
    Allows the PathFollow3D to rotate in any axis.
  ROTATION_ORIENTED = 4
    Uses the up vector information in a Curve3D to enforce orientation. This rotation mode requires the Path3D's Curve3D.up_vector_enabled property to be set to true.
---CHUNK---
Document: PathFollow3D
Path: godot/classes/class_pathfollow3d.rst
Summary: Describes the properties and member variables of the PathFollow3D node in Godot Engine.

Property Descriptions
Property: cubic_interp
Type: bool
Default: true
Setter: set_cubic_interpolation
Getter: get_cubic_interpolation
Description: If true, the position between two cached points is interpolated cubically, and linearly otherwise. The points along the Curve3D of the Path3D are precomputed before use for faster calculations. The point at the requested offset is then calculated by interpolating between two adjacent cached points. This may present a problem if the curve makes sharp turns, as the cached points may not follow the curve closely enough. There are two answers to this problem: either increase the number of cached points and increase memory consumption, or make a cubic interpolation between two points at the cost of slightly slower calculations.

Property: h_offset
Type: float
Default: 0.0
Setter: set_h_offset
Getter: get_h_offset
Description: The node's offset along the curve.

Property: loop
Type: bool
Default: true
Setter: set_loop
Getter: has_loop
Description: If true, any offset outside the path's length will wrap around, instead of stopping at the ends. Use it for cyclic paths.

Property: progress
Type: float
Default: 0.0
Setter: set_progress
Getter: get_progress
Description: The distance from the first vertex, measured in 3D units along the path. Changing this value sets this node's position to a point within the path.

Property: progress_ratio
Type: float
Default: 0.0
Setter: set_progress_ratio
Getter: get_progress_ratio
Description: The distance from the first vertex, considering 0.0 as the first vertex and 1.0 as the last. This is just another way of expressing the progress within the path, as the progress supplied is multiplied internally by the path's length. It can be set or get only if the PathFollow3D is the child of a Path3D which is part of the scene tree, and that this Path3D has a Curve3D with a non-zero length. Otherwise, trying to set this field will print an error, and getting this field will return 0.0.

Property: rotation_mode
Type: RotationMode
Default: 3
Setter: set_rotation_mode
Getter: get_rotation_mode
Description: Allows or forbids rotation on one or more axes, depending on the RotationMode constants being used.

Property: tilt_enabled
Type: bool
Default: true
Setter: set_tilt_enabled
Getter: is_tilt_enabled
Description: If true, the tilt property of Curve3D takes effect.

Property: use_model_front
Type: bool
Default: false
Setter: set_use_model_front
Getter: is_using_model_front
Description: If true, the node moves on the travel path with orienting the +Z axis as forward. See also Vector3.FORWARD and Vector3.MODEL_FRONT.

Property: v_offset
Type: float
Default: 0.0
Setter: set_v_offset
Getter: get_v_offset
Description: The node's offset perpendicular to the curve.
---CHUNK---
